Today was the "AI for Climate & Nature Community Day" at the {{:https://map.cam.ac.uk/?maplon=0.12032&maplat=52.20354&mapzoom=18&maplayers=Building+Labels%2CExternal+Sites%2CColleges%2CUniversity+Sites%2CBuildings%2CTransport&mapfeature=mfid257%2CBuildings}David Attenborough Building}. A whole bunch of the EEG were either presenting or contributing in some way so I thought I'd come along
to see what's going on.


{1 Keynote and main talks}

Following the intro talks from Professors {{:https://www.cambridgeconservation.org/about/people/prof-melissa-leach/}Melissa Leach} and {{:https://www.zoo.cam.ac.uk/directory/bill-sutherland}Bill Sutherland}, the day started with the keynote talk from {{:https://www.biology.ox.ac.uk/people/amy-hinsley}Amy Hinsley}, who, using the specific case of animial trafficking, talked about the need to make AI in conservation equitable, explainable and useful.

