{1 Lightning talks}
We then had a number of 'lightning talks', with each presenter having only three minutes to talk about their work.

- {{:https://www.maths.cam.ac.uk/person/ss3299}Sebastian Schemm} presented his work on creating a foundational model for the climate
- {{:https://www.eng.cam.ac.uk/profiles/ac685}Alice Cicirello} talked about the prospects of applying machine learning to {{:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marine_cloud_brightening}Marine Cloud Brightening}
- {{:https://www.maths.cam.ac.uk/person/sdat2}Simon Thomas} has been looking at analysing the heights of tropical cyclone storm surges
- {{:https://github.com/niccolozanotti}Niccolò Zanotti} gave us an introduction to {{:https://github.com/cambridge-ICCS/FTorch}FTorch}, a library to integrate the worlds of PyTorch and Fortran
- {{:https://www.nceo.ac.uk/contact-us/people/dr-simon-driscoll/}Simon Driscoll} then talked about melt ponds on arctic sea ice, a poorly understood but important component of the climate in the Arctic.
- {{:https://www.zoo.cam.ac.uk/directory/emilio-luz-ricca}Emilio Luz-Ricca} talked about his project to apply machine learning to predict hunting pressure
- {{:https://orlando-code.github.io}Orlando Timmerman} gave us some insights into how he's been using machine learning to predict the future of coral reefs, and how we might use this to help with their conservation.
- {{:https://www.zoo.cam.ac.uk/directory/ruari-marshall-hawkes}Ruari Marshall-Hawkes} showed us how to listen very carefully to figure out population numbers,
- {{:https://www.linkedin.com/in/harriet-branson-a93a8313b/}Hattie Branson} from {{:https://www.fauna-flora.org}Fauna & Flora} talked about habitat detection in South Sudan,
- {{:https://www.linkedin.com/in/martakoch/}Marta Koch} showed us an analysis of how well ChatGPT, Claude and the like would perform at setting the agendas for SDPs,
- {{:https://www.linkedin.com/in/zhengpeng-feng-2410a132a/}Frank Feng} finished the session with a talk on the {{:https://www.cst.cam.ac.uk/seminars/list/227335}Barlow Twins Earth Foundation Model}.

